member.example:
This class can be used as follows:
using (var ctx = new BeginEndEventContext(h => RegisterForEvents(out h), h => UnregisterForEvents(h)))
{
    // Check to see if begin function succeeded
    if (!ctx.BeginSucceeded)
        return;

    // Do some work
}
// End function has been called

member.remarks:
To use this attribute, apply to a structure that defines the handle name.

            /// <summary>A handle to a module.</summary>
            [AutoHandle] // Automatically derives from IHandle
            public partial struct HMODULE { }

            /// <summary>A handle to a synchronization event.</summary>
            [AutoHandle(typeof(ISyncHandle))]
            public partial struct HEVENT
            {
               /// <summary>Sets the signaled state.</summary>
               public bool SetEvent() => SetEvent(handle);
            }

To use this attribute, apply to a structure that defines the handle name.

            /// <summary>A handle to a module.</summary>
